%% Data Flow Diagram - Distributed Workloads
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6
sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Test Suite
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant TrainOp as Training Operator<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    participant KueueCtrl as Kueue Controller<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    participant HeadPod as Head Pod (PyTorch)<br/>29500/TCP
    participant Workers as Worker Pods<br/>29500/TCP NCCL/Gloo
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+

    Note over User,S3: Flow 1: Distributed Training Job Execution
    User->>K8sAPI: Create PyTorchJob CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>TrainOp: Watch event: new PyTorchJob
    TrainOp->>K8sAPI: Create head + worker Pods<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    Workers->>HeadPod: NCCL/Gloo collective comms<br/>29500/TCP plaintext
    HeadPod->>S3: Upload checkpoints<br/>HTTPS/443 AWS IAM

    Note over User,S3: Flow 2: Kueue-Managed Job Scheduling
    User->>K8sAPI: Create ClusterQueue + LocalQueue<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    User->>K8sAPI: Create PyTorchJob (with queue label)<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    KueueCtrl->>K8sAPI: Admit Workload (quota check)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI->>TrainOp: PyTorchJob now admitted
    TrainOp->>K8sAPI: Create training Pods<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token

    participant RayHead as Ray Head<br/>8265/TCP HTTP
    participant RayWorkers as Ray Workers<br/>10001/TCP gRPC
    participant GCS as Ray GCS<br/>6379/TCP

    Note over User,GCS: Flow 3: Ray Job Submission (via Dashboard)
    User->>RayHead: POST /api/jobs/<br/>HTTP/8265 plaintext
    RayHead->>GCS: Store job metadata<br/>TCP/6379 plaintext
    RayHead->>RayWorkers: Dispatch tasks<br/>gRPC/10001 plaintext
    RayWorkers->>S3: Load datasets/models<br/>HTTPS/443 AWS IAM
    RayWorkers-->>RayHead: Task results
    RayHead-->>User: GET /api/jobs/{id}<br/>Job status + logs
